OL,3,CThe Rolling Stones level with The
OL,4,CBeatles after landing 15th UK number
OL,5,Cone album
OL,7,FThe track has overtaken Bryan Adams'
OL,8,Flong-running number one (Everything I
OL,9,FDo) I Do It For You, which sat at the
OL,10,Ftop of the charts for 16 consecutive
OL,11,Fweeks in 1991.
OL,13,FIt is one week away from equalling
OL,14,FFrankie Laine's 1953 hit I Believe in
OL,15,Fenjoying the most weeks at number one
OL,16,Fever, and was recently crowned the
OL,17,Flongest-running number one single of
OL,18,Fall time by a British act.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/11
